<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott
Laboratories and Subsidiaries</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Condensed
Consolidated Statement of Earnings</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited)</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">(dollars
and shares in thousands except per share data)</font></i></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott
Laboratories and Subsidiaries</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Condensed

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

in thousands)</font></i></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott Laboratories
and Subsidiaries</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited)</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 1.8pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 1 &#151; Basis of
Presentation</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 1.8pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 9.9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The accompanying
unaudited, condensed consolidated financial statements have been prepared
pursuant to rules&nbsp;and regulations of the Securities and Exchange
Commission and, therefore, do not include all information and footnote
disclosures normally included in audited financial statements.&#160; However, in the opinion of management, all
adjustments (which include only normal adjustments) necessary to present fairly
the results of operations, financial position and cash flows have been
made.&#160; It is suggested that these
statements be read in conjunction with the financial statements included in
Abbott&#146;s Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31,
2008.&#160; Events that occurred after June&nbsp;30,
2009 through the date that these financial statements have been filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission were considered in the preparation of these
financial statements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 9.9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On January&nbsp;1, 2009,
Abbott adopted SFAS No.&nbsp;160 &#147;<em><i><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-style:normal;">Noncontrolling Interests in Consolidated Financial
Statements&#151;an amendment of ARB No.&nbsp;51&#148; and accordingly, noncontrolling
interests in subsidiaries are presented as a component of total equity as of June&nbsp;30,
2009 and December&nbsp;31, 2008.</font></i></em></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 2 &#151;
Supplemental Financial Information</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Other (income) expense,
net, for the first six months of 2009 includes the derecognition of a
contingent liability of $797 million associated with the conclusion of the TAP
joint venture as discussed in Note 9 and income from the recording of certain
investments at fair value in connection with business acquisitions.&#160; Other (income) expense, net, for the second
quarter and first six months of 2009 and 2008 includes ongoing contractual payments
from Takeda associated with the conclusion of the TAP joint venture.&#160; In connection with the dissolution of the TAP
Pharmaceutical Products Inc. joint venture, Abbott recorded a gain of
approximately $95 million in the second quarter 2008, which is included in
Other (income) expense, net.&#160; Other
(income) expense, net for the second quarter and six months ended June&nbsp;30,
2008 also includes a gain of approximately $52 million on the sale of an equity
investment accounted for as an available-for-sale investment.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Supplemental Cash Flow
Information &#151; Other, net in Net cash from operating activities for 2009 and
2008 includes the effects of contributions to the main domestic defined benefit
plan of $700 million and $200 million, respectively, and to the post-employment
medical and dental plans of $13 million and $65 million in 2009 and 2008,
respectively.&#160; Purchases of other
investment securities, net in 2009 and 2008 reflects the acquisition of
short-term investments with original maturities of over three months.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The components of
long-term investments as of June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31, 2008 are
as follows:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .2in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 3 &#151; Taxes on
Earnings</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Taxes on earnings
reflect the estimated annual effective rates and include charges for interest
and penalties.&#160; The effective tax rates
are less than the statutory U.S. federal income tax rate principally due to the
benefit of lower statutory tax rates and tax exemptions in several foreign
taxing jurisdictions.&#160; In the second
quarter of 2008, Abbott&#146;s federal income tax returns for 2004 and 2005 were
settled, resulting in a net reduction of income taxes of approximately $30
million.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .2in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 4 &#151;
Litigation and Environmental Matters</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott has been
identified as a potentially responsible party for investigation and cleanup
costs at a number of locations in the United States and Puerto Rico under
federal and state remediation laws and is investigating potential contamination
at a number of company-owned locations.&#160;
Abbott has recorded an estimated cleanup cost for each site for which
management believes Abbott has a probable loss exposure.&#160; No individual site cleanup exposure is
expected to exceed $3&nbsp;million, and the aggregate cleanup exposure is not
expected to exceed $15&nbsp;million.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There are a number of
patent disputes with third parties who claim Abbott&#146;s products infringe their
patents.&nbsp; In April&nbsp;2007, New York University (NYU) and Centocor,&nbsp;Inc.
filed a lawsuit in the Eastern District of Texas asserting that <i>HUMIRA</i> infringes a patent co-owned by NYU
and Centocor.&#160; In June&nbsp;2009, a jury
found that Abbott had willfully infringed the patent and awarded NYU and
Centocor approximately $1.67 billion in past compensatory damages.&#160; The award is subject to review by the trial
court.&#160; Abbott will ask the trial court
to overturn the verdict and/or reduce the damages award.&#160; In the event that the trial court does not
overturn the verdict, Abbott will appeal.&#160;
Abbott is confident in the merits of its case and believes that it will
prevail on appeal.&#160; As a result, no
reserves have been recorded in this case.&#160;
Abbott&#146;s acquisition of Kos Pharmaceuticals Inc. resulted in the
assumption of various cases and investigations and Abbott has recorded reserves
related to several of those cases and investigations.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There are several civil
actions pending brought by individuals or entities that allege generally that
Abbott and numerous pharmaceutical companies reported false or misleading
pricing information relating to the average wholesale price of certain
pharmaceutical products in connection with federal, state and private
reimbursement.&#160; Civil actions have also
been brought against Abbott, and in some cases other members of the
pharmaceutical industry, by state attorneys general seeking to recover alleged
damages on behalf of state Medicaid programs.&#160;
In May&nbsp;2006, Abbott was notified that the U.S. Department of
Justice intervened in a civil whistle-blower lawsuit alleging that Abbott
inflated prices for Medicaid and Medicare reimbursable drugs.&#160; Abbott has settled a few of the cases and
recorded reserves for its estimated losses in a few other cases, however,
Abbott is unable to estimate the range or amount of possible loss for the
remaining cases, and no loss reserves have been recorded for them.&#160; Many of the products involved in these cases
are Hospira products.&#160; Hospira, Abbott&#146;s
former hospital products business, was spun off to Abbott&#146;s shareholders in
2004.&#160; Abbott retained liability for
losses that result from these cases and investigations to the extent any such
losses both relate to the sale of Hospira&#146;s products prior to the spin-off of
Hospira and relate to allegations that were made in such pending and future
cases and investigations that were the same as allegations existing at the date
of the spin-off.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There
are several civil actions pending brought by state attorneys general and
private entities alleging antitrust and unfair competition claims in connection
with the sales of <i>TriCor</i>. Abbott
licenses <i>TriCor</i> from a third
party and the licensor has also been named as a defendant.&#160; Settlements have been reached in all of these
cases except the state attorneys general, however, Abbott is unable to estimate
a reserve and no loss reserve has been recorded for the remaining <i>TriCor</i> cases.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Within the next year,
legal proceedings may occur that may result in a change in the estimated
reserves recorded by Abbott.&nbsp; For its legal proceedings and environmental
exposures, except as noted above, Abbott estimates the range of possible loss
to be from approximately $205 million to $415 million.&#160; The recorded reserve balance at June&nbsp;30,
2009 for these proceedings and exposures was approximately $275 million.&#160; These reserves represent management&#146;s best
estimate of probable loss, as defined by Statement of Financial Accounting
Standards No.&nbsp;5 &#147;Accounting for Contingencies.&#148;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">While it is not feasible to predict the
outcome of all such proceedings and exposures with certainty, management
believes that their ultimate disposition should not have a material adverse
effect on Abbott&#146;s financial position, cash flows, or results of operations,
except for the cases and investigations discussed in the third paragraph and
the patent case discussed in the second paragraph of this footnote, the
resolution of which could be material to cash flows or results of operations.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">6</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<p style="margin:0in .2in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 5 &#151;

defined contribution, and medical and dental plans.&#160; Net cost for the three and six months ended June&nbsp;30
for Abbott&#146;s major defined benefit plans and post-employment medical and dental
benefit plans is as follows:</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott funds its domestic defined benefit
plans according to IRS funding limitations.&#160;
In the first quarters of 2009 and 2008, $700 million and $200 million,
respectively, was contributed to the main domestic defined benefit plan and $13
million and $65 million, respectively, was contributed to the post-employment
medical and dental benefit plans.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7</font></p>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='7',FILE='C:\JMS\105932\09-13597-1\task3657782\13597-1-ba-05.htm',USER='105932',CD='Aug  4 09:31 2009' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .2in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 7 &#151; Segment
Information</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .7pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s principal
business is the discovery, development, manufacture and sale of a broad line of
health care products.&#160; Abbott&#146;s products
are generally sold directly to retailers, wholesalers, hospitals, health care
facilities, laboratories, physicians&#146; offices and government agencies
throughout the world.&#160; Abbott&#146;s
reportable segments are as follows:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .7pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Pharmaceutical
Products</font></i> &#151; Worldwide sales of a broad line of
pharmaceuticals.&#160; For segment reporting
purposes, two pharmaceutical divisions are aggregated and reported as the
Pharmaceutical Products segment.</p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Nutritional
Products</font></i> &#151; Worldwide sales of a broad line of adult and
pediatric nutritional products.</p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Diagnostic Products</font></i>
&#151; Worldwide sales of diagnostic systems and tests for blood banks, hospitals,
commercial laboratories and alternate-care testing sites.&#160; For segment reporting purposes, three
diagnostic divisions are aggregated and reported as the Diagnostic Products
segment.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Vascular</font></i>
<i>Products</i>&nbsp;&#151; Worldwide sales of
coronary, endovascular, vessel closure and other products.</p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s underlying
accounting records are maintained on a legal entity basis for government and
public reporting requirements.&#160; Segment
disclosures are on a performance basis consistent with internal management
reporting.&#160; Intersegment transfers of
inventory are recorded at standard cost and are not a measure of segment
operating earnings.&#160; The cost of some
corporate functions and the cost of certain employee benefits are charged to
segments at predetermined rates that approximate cost.&#160; Remaining costs, if any, are not allocated to
segments. <b>&#160;</b>For acquisitions prior to 2006,
substantially all intangible assets and related amortization are not allocated
to segments.<b>&#160;
</b>The following segment information has been prepared in
accordance with the internal accounting policies of Abbott, as described above,
and are not presented in accordance with generally accepted accounting
principles applied to the consolidated financial statements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="1" width="25%" noshade color="black" align="left"></div>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Approximately 40 to 45
percent of the annual net cost of share-based awards will typically be
recognized in the first quarter due to the timing of the granting of
share-based awards.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Other, net, for the six
months ended June&nbsp;30, 2009, includes the derecognition of a contingent
liability of $797 established in connection with the conclusion of the TAP
joint venture.&#160; Other, net for the three
months and six months ended June&nbsp;30, 2008, includes the gain from the
closing of the TAP joint venture and contractual payments from TAP associated
with the closing of the TAP Pharmaceutical Products Inc. joint venture.</p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">8</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .2in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 8 &#151; Incentive Stock
Program</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 1.45pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In the first six
months of 2009, Abbott granted 1,712,400 stock options, 797,763 replacement
stock options, 1,274,400 restricted stock awards and 5,468,552 restricted stock
units under this program.&#160; In addition,
2,899,411 options were issued in connection with the conversion of Advanced
Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc. options to Abbott options.&#160;&#160; At June&nbsp;30, 2009, approximately
220&nbsp;million shares were reserved for future grants, including 175 million
shares authorized by Abbott&#146;s shareholders in April&nbsp;2009.&#160; Information regarding the number of options
outstanding and exercisable at June&nbsp;30, 2009 is as follows:</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The total unrecognized
share-based compensation cost at June&nbsp;30, 2009 amounted to approximately
$340 million which is expected to be recognized over the next three years.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 9 &#151;
Conclusion of TAP Pharmaceutical Products Inc. Joint Venture</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 62.3pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On April&nbsp;30, 2008,
Abbott and Takeda concluded their TAP Pharmaceutical Products Inc. (TAP) joint
venture, evenly splitting the value and assets of the joint venture.&#160; Abbott exchanged its 50 percent equity
interest in TAP for the assets, liabilities and employees related to TAP&#146;s <i>Lupron</i> business.&#160; Beginning on May&nbsp;1, 2008, Abbott began
recording U.S. <i>Lupron</i> net sales
and costs in its operating results and no longer records income from the TAP
joint venture.&#160; Abbott receives payments
based on specified development, approval and commercial events being achieved
with respect to products retained by Takeda and payments from Takeda based on
sales of products retained by Takeda, which are recorded by Abbott as Other
(income) expense, net as earned.&#160; Abbott
also agreed to remit cash to Takeda if certain research and development events
were not achieved on the development assets retained by Takeda.&#160; These amounts were recorded as a liability at
closing in the amount of approximately $1.1 billion.&#160; Of the $1.1 billion, Abbott made
tax-deductible payments of $83 million and $200 million in 2009 and 2008,
respectively, and Abbott will make a tax-deductible payment of approximately
$36 million in 2010.&#160; In the first
quarter of 2009, events occurred resulting in certain payments not being
required and a liability in the amount of $797 million was derecognized and
recorded as income in Other (income) expense, net.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The 50 percent-owned
joint venture was accounted for under the equity method of accounting.&#160; Summarized financial information for TAP for
the three months and six months ended June&nbsp;30, 2008 are as follows below:
(<i>dollars in millions</i>)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .2in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 10 &#151; Business
Acquisitions</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In February&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired the outstanding shares of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc.
(AMO), a marketer of ophthalmic surgical technology and devices, as well as eye
care solutions for approximately $1.4 billion in cash, net of cash held by
AMO.&#160; Prior to the acquisition, Abbott
held a small investment in AMO.&#160; Abbott
acquired AMO to take advantage of increasing demand for vision care
technologies due to population growth and demographic shifts and AMO&#146;s premier
position in its field.&#160; Abbott acquired
control of this business on February&nbsp;25, 2009 and the financial results of
the acquired operations are included in these financial statements beginning on
that date in accordance with Statement of Financial Accounting Standards No.&nbsp;141(R).&#160; The acquisition was financed with long-term
debt.&#160; The preliminary allocation of the
fair value of the acquisition is shown in the table below <i>(in billions of dollars)</i>.&nbsp; These
allocations will be finalized when appraisals are completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="66%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:66.66%;">
 <tr>
  <td width="76%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:76.74%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.0pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Goodwill,
  non-deductible</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.76%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.94%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$</font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="16%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;border-left:none;border-right:none;border-top:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:16.06%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.4</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.48%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquired
intangible assets consist of established customer relationships, developed
technology and trade names and will be amortized over 2 to 30 years (average of
15 years).&#160; Acquired in-process research
and development will be accounted for as an indefinite lived intangible asset
until regulatory approval or discontinuation.&#160;
The net tangible assets acquired consist primarily of trade accounts
receivable, inventory, property and equipment and other assets, net of assumed
liabilities, primarily trade accounts payable, accrued compensation and other
liabilities.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott incurred
approximately $70 million of acquisition related expenses in the first six
months of 2009 which are classified as Selling, general and administrative
expense.&#160; In addition, subsequent to the
acquisition, Abbott repaid substantially all of the acquired debt of AMO.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In January&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired Ibis Biosciences,&nbsp;Inc. (Ibis) for $175 million, in cash,
to expand Abbott&#146;s position in molecular diagnostics for infectious
disease.&#160; Including a $40 million
investment in Ibis in 2008, Abbott has acquired 100 percent of the outstanding
shares of Ibis.&#160; A substantial portion of
the fair value of the acquisition has been allocated to goodwill and
amortizable intangible assets, and acquired in-process research and development
which will be accounted for as an indefinite lived intangible asset until
regulatory approval or discontinuation.&#160;
The investment in Ibis in 2008 resulted in a charge to acquired in-process
research and development in the first six months of 2008.&#160; In connection with the acquisition, the
carrying amount of this investment was revalued to fair value in the first
quarter of 2009 resulting in recording $33 million of income, which is reported
as Other (income) expense, net.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Had the above acquisitions taken place on January&nbsp;1
of the previous year, consolidated net sales and income would not have been
significantly different from reported amounts.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='10',FILE='C:\JMS\105932\09-13597-1\task3657782\13597-1-ba-05.htm',USER='105932',CD='Aug  4 09:31 2009' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed Consolidated Financial
Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 11 &#151;
Financial Instruments, Derivatives and Fair Value Measures</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Certain Abbott
foreign subsidiaries enter into foreign currency forward exchange contracts to
manage exposures to changes in foreign exchange rates for anticipated
intercompany purchases by those subsidiaries whose functional currencies are
not the U.S. dollar.&#160; These contracts,
totaling $470<b>  </b>million and $129
million at June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31, 2008, respectively, are
designated as cash flow hedges of the variability of the cash flows due to
changes in foreign exchange rates.<b>&#160; </b>Accumulated gains and losses as of
June&nbsp;30, 2009 will be included in Cost of products sold at the time the
products are sold, generally through the next twelve months.&#160; The amount of hedge ineffectiveness was not
significant in 2009 and 2008 for these hedges.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott enters into foreign currency forward
exchange contracts to manage currency exposures for foreign currency
denominated third-party trade payables and receivables, and for intercompany
loans and trade accounts payable where the receivable or payable is denominated
in a currency other than the functional currency of the entity.&#160; For intercompany loans, the contracts require
Abbott to sell or buy foreign currencies, primarily European currencies and
Japanese yen, in exchange for primarily U.S. dollars and other European
currencies.&#160; For intercompany and trade
payables and receivables, the currency exposures are primarily the U.S. dollar,
European currencies and Japanese yen.&#160; At
June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31, 2008, Abbott held $6.5 billion and
$8.3 billion, respectively, of such foreign currency forward exchange
contracts.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott has designated foreign denominated
short-term debt as a hedge of the net investment in certain foreign
subsidiaries of approximately $556 million and approximately $585 million as of
June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31, 2008, respectively.&#160; Accordingly, changes in the fair value of
this debt due to changes in exchange rates are recorded in Accumulated other
comprehensive income (loss), net of tax.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott is a party to interest rate swap
contracts totaling $5.5 billion and $2.5 billion at June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31,
2008, respectively, to manage its exposure to changes in the fair value of $5.5
billion and $2.5 billion, respectively, of fixed-rate debt due 2011 through
2019.&#160; These contracts are designated as
fair value hedges of the variability of the fair value of fixed-rate debt due
to changes in the long-term benchmark interest rates.&#160; The effect of the hedge is to change a
fixed-rate interest obligation to a variable rate for that portion of the
debt.&#160; Abbott records the contracts at
fair value and adjusts the carrying amount of the fixed-rate debt by an
offsetting amount.&#160; No hedge
ineffectiveness was recorded in income in 2009 or 2008 for these hedges.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following table
summarizes the amounts and location of certain derivative financial instruments
as of June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31, 2008:</font></p>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&#151;</font></p>
  </td>

<div>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:hanging;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed Consolidated Financial
Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following table
summarizes the activity for foreign currency forward exchange contracts
designated as cash flow hedges, debt designated as a hedge of net investment in
certain foreign subsidiaries and the amounts and location of income (expense)
and gain (loss) reclassified into income in the second quarter and first six
months of 2009 and 2008 and for certain other derivative financial instruments.&#160; The amount of hedge ineffectiveness was not
significant in 2009 and 2008 for these hedges.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The carrying values and
fair values of certain financial instruments as of June&nbsp;30, 2009 and December&nbsp;31,
2008 are shown in the table below. The carrying values of all other financial
instruments approximate their estimated fair values.&#160; The counterparties to financial instruments
consist of select major international financial institutions. Abbott does not
expect any losses from nonperformance by these counterparties.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following table
summarizes the bases used to measure certain assets and liabilities at fair value
on a recurring basis in the balance sheet:</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

 <tr>
  <td width="43%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:43.64%;">

  </td>
  <td width="10%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:10.0%;">

  </td>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The value of the
financial assets and liabilities relating to TAP employees&#146; stock options are
calculated using the Black-Scholes option-pricing model.&#160; Changes in the recorded amounts are recorded
in Other income (expense), net each period.&#160;
The recorded value of investments that are valued using significant
unobservable inputs did not change significantly.&#160; Changes in these values are recorded in
Accumulated other comprehensive income.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note&nbsp;12&nbsp;</font>&#151; Goodwill and Intangible Assets</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott recorded goodwill
of approximately $1.7 billion in 2009 related to the acquisitions of Advanced
Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc. and Ibis Biosciences,&nbsp;Inc.&#160; In connection with the dissolution of the TAP
Pharmaceutical Products Inc. (TAP) joint venture in 2008, Abbott recorded
approximately $350 million of goodwill. Goodwill related to the Ibis
acquisition was allocated to the Diagnostic Products segment and goodwill
related to TAP was allocated to the Pharmaceutical Products segment.&#160; Foreign currency translation adjustments and other
adjustments increased goodwill in the first six months of 2009 and 2008 by
approximately $506<b>  </b>million and
$312 million, respectively.&#160; The amount
of goodwill related to reportable segments at June&nbsp;30, 2009 was $6.3
billion for the Pharmaceutical Products segment, $206 million for the Nutritional
Products segment, $386 million for the Diagnostic Products segment and $2.4
billion for the Vascular Products segment.&#160;
There were no reductions of goodwill relating to impairments or disposal
of all or a portion of a business.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The gross amount of amortizable
intangible assets, primarily product rights and technology, was $10.6 billion<b>  </b>as of June&nbsp;30, 2009 and $9.4 billion
as of December&nbsp;31, 2008, and accumulated amortization was $4.6 billion as
of June&nbsp;30, 2009 and $4.2 billion as of December&nbsp;31, 2008.&#160; The estimated annual amortization expense for
intangible assets is approximately $847 million in 2009, $859 million in 2010,
$844 million in 2011, $831 million in 2012 and $675 million in 2013.
Amortizable intangible assets are amortized over 4 to 25&nbsp;years (average 11
years).</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">13</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 45.0pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2009</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited),
continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 13 &#151;
Restructuring Plans</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In 2008, Abbott
management approved a plan to streamline global manufacturing operations,
reduce overall costs, and improve efficiencies in Abbott&#146;s core diagnostic
business.&#160; Additional charges of
approximately $23 million were recorded in the first six months of 2009
relating to this restructuring, primarily for accelerated depreciation and
product transfer costs.&#160; Additional
charges will occur through 2011 as a result of product re-registration
timelines required under manufacturing regulations in a number of countries and
product transition timelines.&#160; The following
summarizes the activity for this restructuring:&#160;
<i>(dollars in millions)</i></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In 2009 and prior
years, Abbott management approved plans to realign its worldwide pharmaceutical
and vascular manufacturing operations and selected domestic and international
commercial and research and development operations in order to reduce costs.&#160; Additional charges of $20 million and $44
million were subsequently recorded in the first six months of 2009 and 2008,
respectively, relating to these restructurings, primarily for accelerated
depreciation and product transfer costs.&#160;
The following summarizes the activity for these restructurings: <i>(dollars in millions)</i></font></p>

  </td>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">)</font></p>

  balance at June&nbsp;30</font></p>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">146</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 14 &#151; Subsequent
Event &#151; Litigation Settlement</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;vertical-align:baseline;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">In July&nbsp;2009,
Abbott and Medtronic,&nbsp;Inc. reached a settlement resolving all outstanding
intellectual property litigation between the two parties.&#160; Under the terms of the settlement, Medtronic
will pay Abbott $400 million.&#160; The
settlement also includes a mutual agreement not to pursue additional litigation
on current and future vascular products, subject to specific conditions and
time limits.&#160; The one-time impact of this
settlement will be included in third quarter 2009 earnings.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">14</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">23.9</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Worldwide sales
for the second quarter and the first six months of 2009 compared to 2008
reflect the negative effect of a relatively stronger U.S. dollar.&#160; Excluding 8.0 percent and 7.1 percent of
unfavorable exchange for the second quarter and first six months of 2009, net
sales increased 10.5 percent and 8.0 percent, respectively, which reflects
primarily unit growth.&#160; The relatively
stronger U.S. dollar decreased second quarter 2009 Total International sales by
14.9 percent, Pharmaceutical Products segment sales by 8.3 percent, Nutritional
Product segment sales by 5.2 percent, Diagnostic Products segment sales by 10.1
percent and Vascular Products segment sales by 8.7 percent over the second
quarter of 2008.&#160; The relatively stronger
U.S. dollar decreased the first six months 2009 Total International sales by
13.0 percent, Pharmaceutical Products segment sales by 7.5 percent, Nutritional
Product segment sales by 4.7 percent, Diagnostic Products segment sales by 9.0
percent and Vascular Products segment sales by 6.7 percent over the first six
months of 2008.&#160; The relatively weaker
U.S. dollar increased second quarter 2008 consolidated net sales by 5.9
percent, Total International sales by 12.0 percent, Pharmaceutical Products
segment sales by 6.0 percent, Nutritional Product segment sales by 3.6 percent,
Diagnostic Products segment sales by 9.2 percent and Vascular Products segment
sales by 6.4 percent over the second quarter of 2007.&#160; The relatively weaker U.S. dollar also
increased the first six months 2008 consolidated net sales by 5.7 percent,
Total International sales by 11.5 percent, Pharmaceutical Products segment
sales by 6.0 percent, Nutritional Product segment sales by 3.3 percent,
Diagnostic Products segment sales by 8.7 percent and Vascular Products segment
sales by 5.6 percent over the first six months of 2007.&#160; The sales growth in 2009 for the Vascular Products
segment was impacted by the U.S. launch of the <i>Xience
V </i>drug eluting stent in the third quarter of 2008.&#160; The sales growth in 2009 for the
Pharmaceutical Products segment and Total U.S. sales in 2009 were impacted by
decreased sales of <i>Depakote </i>due to
generic competition.&#160; The increase in
Other sales for the second quarter of 2009 is primarily due to the acquisition
of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc. on February&nbsp;25, 2009.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">15</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A comparison of
significant product group sales for the six months ended June&nbsp;30 is as
follows.&#160; Percent changes are versus the
prior year and are based on unrounded numbers.</font></p>

  </td>

  <td width="11%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:11.26%;">

  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.12%;">

  </td>
  <td width="11%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:11.26%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <td width="247" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="10" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="58" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="67" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="10" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="58" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="67" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="7" style="border:none;"></td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Decreased sales of
<i>Depakote</i> due to generic
competition impacted U.S. Specialty product sales in 2009.&#160; This was partially offset by increased sales
of <i>HUMIRA</i> and by the addition of <i>Lupron </i>sales from the conclusion of the
TAP joint venture in April&nbsp;2008.&#160;
U.S. sales of <i>Depakote</i> for
the first six months of 2009 and 2008 were $190 million and $727 million,
respectively.&#160; Increased sales of <i>HUMIRA</i> and <i>Depakote</i> accounted for the majority of the sales increases
for U.S. Specialty products in 2008.&#160;
U.S. Primary Care sales in both 2009 and 2008 were impacted by decreased
sales of <i>Omnicef </i>and <i>Synthroid</i> due to generic competition,
partially offset by increased sales of <i>Niaspan</i>
and the <i>TriCor/Trilipix </i>franchise.&#160; Increased sales of <i>HUMIRA</i> favorably impacted International Pharmaceutical sales
in both 2009 and 2008.&#160; International
sales of <i>HUMIRA</i> for the first six
months of 2009 and 2008 were $1.290 billion and $1.039 billion,
respectively.&#160; Abbott forecasts 2009
worldwide <i>HUMIRA</i> sales growth of
15 to 20 percent. Excluding the impact of exchange, Abbott forecasts 2009 <i>HUMIRA</i> sales growth of 25 to 30
percent.&#160; The relatively stronger U.S.
dollar decreased International Pharmaceutical sales in 2009 by 14.3 percent and
the relatively weaker U.S. dollar increased International Pharmaceutical sales
in 2008 by 12.9 percent.&#160; International
Pediatric Nutritionals sales increases in 2009 and 2008 were due primarily to
volume growth in developing countries.&#160;
The relatively stronger U.S. dollar decreased International Adult
Nutritionals sales in 2009 by 11.9 percent and the relatively weaker U.S.
dollar increased International Adult Nutritionals sales in 2008 by 9.0
percent.&#160;&#160; The relatively stronger U.S.
dollar decreased Immunochemistry sales in 2009 by 9.7 percent and the
relatively weaker U.S. dollar increased Immunochemistry sales in 2008 by 9.5
percent.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The gross profit
margin was 58.3 percent for the
second quarter 2009, compared to 57.3 percent for the second quarter 2008.&#160; First six months 2009 gross profit margin was
57.3 percent, compared to 56.8 percent for the first six months 2008.&#160; The gross profit margin for the first six
months 2009 was impacted by charges relating to a delayed product launch and
the discontinuation of a product.&#160; These
charges had the effect of reducing the gross profit margin by 0.6 percentage
points.&#160; The increases in the gross
profit margin in 2009, excluding these charges, were due, in part, to improved
margins in the vascular and diagnostics businesses and the favorable effect of
exchange on the gross profit margin ratio; partially offset by the negative
impact from lower sales of <i>Depakote</i>.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Research and
development expenses increased 2.0
percent in the second quarter 2009 and 3.5
percent for the first six months 2009 over comparable 2008 periods.&#160; These increases reflect continued pipeline
spending, including programs in vascular devices, biologics, neuroscience,
oncology and Hepatitis C.&#160; The majority
of research and development expenditures is concentrated on pharmaceutical
products.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Selling, general
and administrative expenses for the second quarter 2009 decreased 1.4 percent and increased 0.6 percent for the first six months of
2009 over the comparable 2008 periods.&#160;&#160;
These changes reflect the favorable effect of exchange rates which was
offset by expenses relating to the acquisition of Advanced Medical Optics, Inc,
and the settlement of litigation in the first six months of 2009.&#160; Excluding the effect of the charges and
exchange, selling, general and administrative expenses increased 6.3 percent
and 3.1 percent for the second quarter 2009 and first six months of 2009,
respectively.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">16</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .5in .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Business
Acquisitions</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In February&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired the outstanding shares of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc.
(AMO), a marketer of ophthalmic surgical technology and devices, as well as eye
care solutions for approximately $1.4 billion in cash, net of cash held by
AMO.&#160; Prior to the acquisition, Abbott
held a small investment in AMO.&#160; Abbott
acquired AMO to take advantage of increasing demand for vision care
technologies due to population growth and demographic shifts and AMO&#146;s premier
position in its field.&#160; Abbott acquired
control of this business on February&nbsp;25, 2009 and the financial results of
the acquired operations are included in these financial statements beginning on
that date in accordance with Statement of Financial Accounting Standards No.&nbsp;141(R).&#160; The acquisition was financed with long-term
debt.&#160; The preliminary allocation of the
fair value of the acquisition is shown in the table below <i>(in billions of dollars)</i>.&nbsp; These
allocations will be finalized when appraisals are completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in .9pt .0001pt 0in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <td width="74%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:74.16%;">
